@mcg1969 I think you are right: this issue belongs somewhere else.  I posted it here because  I felt like the opportunity to figure out how to fix the problem is more likely to come from the conda team who can think clearly about this scenario and what could be done and what should be done, rather than attempting to put it on the Jupyter team to resolve.

This is a very real issue that impacts Conda usage.  I do think it is OK for us to just say "Other people need to do it our way" (IOW, in a way compatible with conda environments).  But it would be helpful if, in high value situations like this (Jupyter extensions), we were prepared to articulate the details of what "our way" looks like, and perhaps (again, in situations like this) even go so far as to figure out and document what we believe is the "best practice" way to deal with software configuration in a manner that is compatible with Conda environments.

